<h4>The Inca</h4>
<p>The Inca showed up in Cusco around 1300 CE, pretty late in the game (And not too long before the game ended in 1572 with conquering and terrifying plagues that emptied the continent). They had big stretched lobes, bigger than even what you’d see in the Mayan or Moche cultures. They were depicted by Spanish artists, and in their own pottery, as having lobes that went nearly down to their shoulders.</p>
<figure class="figure float-right ml-5" style="width:255px">
	<img class="figure-img img-fluid" src="images/2016/05/inca-15th-cent-met.jpg" />
	<figcaption class="figure-caption">These are solid silver plugs from the 15th century. In archeological documents, these are often called "ear spools". But they're plugs. (Image credit: MetMuseum.org)</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Ceremonial jars and sculptures show members of the Inca elite wearing both giant plugs in their ears, and leaving their lobes empty to dangle, so both of these were in fashion. The Inca were unisex when it came to stretching, with both men and women being depicted with stretched lobes.</p>


