<p><strong>India Bonus!</strong></p>
<p>I can’t talk about India without mentioning one of the most famous stretched lobe having people in the history of the world: Siddhartha Gautama, AKA <em>the Buddha</em>. He lived sometime around the 5th century BCE and had <em>huge</em> stretched lobes. In statues of him, the lobes hang loose, often down to his shoulders. The story goes that as a wealthy prince, Siddhartha wore expensive plugs in his lobes, and when he gave all that up</p>


<p>to follow the path of enlightenment he threw them away, leaving his lobes empty. Depicting the Buddha with stretched lobes is actually part of the iconography of Buddhism, and can have many different spiritual interpretations. Interestingly, in Mahayana Buddhism, which is popular across Asia, the Bodhisattvas who have achieved enlightenment are also depicted with stretched lobes, even though they may come from other cultures.</p>
